cs.CG, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.GR, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with computational geometry and numerical methods for solving differential equations on meshes, which suggests cs.CG (Computational Geometry) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of discrete exterior calculus (DEC), which falls under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper's impact in computer graphics suggests cs.GR (Graphics) as a possible sub-category.
